    <a title="Phrynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne"><img alt="Phrynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640891977p2/8655084.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1244480138?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phrynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phrynne" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne">Phrynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781444775839" href="/book/show/24407979-my-grandmother-sends-her-regards-and-apologises">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1244480138" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14331079004601149895">I seem to have ageist issues with this author&apos;s books. In <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18774964.A_Man_Called_Ove' title='A Man Called Ove by Fredrik Backman' rel='nofollow noopener'>A Man Called Ove</a> the main character was in his fifties and acted like a man of 85. In this book the main character is seven and acts as if she is 17. However if I ignore that I did enjoy the story and found it to be a light, entertaining read, not quite as interesting as Ove, but still okay.</span>
  <span id="freeText14331079004601149895" style="display:none">I seem to have ageist issues with this author's books. In <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18774964.A_Man_Called_Ove" title="A Man Called Ove by Fredrik Backman" rel="nofollow noopener">A Man Called Ove</a> the main character was in his fifties and acted like a man of 85. In this book the main character is seven and acts as if she is 17. However if I ignore that I did enjoy the story and found it to be a light, entertaining read, not quite as interesting as Ove, but still okay.</span>
